http://www.teaparty07.com/
 
 Anyone want to take bets as to what today's "money bomb" will bring in?
 
 The organiser was hoping for $6 million, which is about what the signups would indicate.
 
 Early trend lines would suggest something closer to $10 million, though it's too early to tell whether the pattern of donations will closely match that on November 5th.
 
 http://www.ronpaulgraphs.com/dec_16_vs_nov_5_total.html
 
 I'll say 10 million, since I've tended to heavily underestimate these things in the past, bringing Paul to around $21 million for the quarter so far.

$6.6 million looks like the official total, including offline contributions, beating Kerry's 2004 record of $5.7 million, the day AFTER he got the nomination from the democratic party.
 
 It's strange isn't it, for a candidate that does only 6 or 10% in the polls, has this depth of support, 55,000 donors in one day.
